Reasons To Stop
Although I said many times that the main beneficiary from this blog is me, I still however care about the opinions of the people reading my posts (there‚Äôs only about 10 currently) and for some reason there was relatively low feed back especially for the last post and I started thinking the wrong way (like I always do) which is that because how uninteresting they are. I thought ‚Äúno one asked and no one cares about your opinions, they only interacted with first ones out of pity and now got bored from pretending to care‚Äù.</p>

